# Static Rope Node Injection Implementation Plan

## Goal Description
Implement automatic injection of rope climbing nodes into the path data. The system should detect vertical gaps in the recorded path and bridge them using static rope data defined in the map, inserting [ClimbUp](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/Core/PathPlanningTracker.cs#2147-2171) and `Walk` (exit) nodes.

## Proposed Changes

### Core Logic
#### [MODIFY] [PathPlanningTracker.cs](file:///d:/Full_end/C#/ArtaleAI/Core/PathPlanningTracker.cs)
- [x] Create [InjectRopeNodes()](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/Core/PathPlanningTracker.cs#554-671) method.
    - **Logic Refined**: 
        - Iterate to find next valid (non-Break) node.
        - Scan path segments and find matching [RopeData](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/Models/PathPlanning/RopeData.cs#6-28) where:
            - `Abs(Rope.X - Path.X) < 50`
            - `Abs(Rope.BottomY - Path.Start.Y) < 30`
            - `Abs(Rope.TopY - Path.End.Y) < 50`
        - If matching rope found:
            - Insert [ClimbUp](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/Core/PathPlanningTracker.cs#2147-2171) node (Keys=["up"]) at rope bottom.
            - Insert exit node (Keys=[]) at rope top.
            - **Remove** intervening `Break` nodes to create continuous path.
- [x] Call [InjectRopeNodes()](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/Core/PathPlanningTracker.cs#554-671) in [InitializePathState](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/Core/PathPlanningTracker.cs#499-541).
- [x] Remove dynamic rope lookahead logic to enforce strict sequential navigation.

#### [MODIFY] [PathNode.cs](file:///d:/Full_end/C#/ArtaleAI/Core/PathNode.cs)
- [x] Verified [Action](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/UI/MainForm.cs#108-125) property is read-only and derived from [Keys](file:///d:/Full_end/C%23/ArtaleAI/Core/PathPlanningTracker.cs#481-506).

